XML: Extensible Markup Language
- XML is used to exchange data or structure data
- XML uses user defined tags. XML does not have predefined tags
- XML tags are case sensitive
- XML tags must be closed otherwise you will get an error
- XML is a strict Language
- XML file must have .xml extension
- XML tags name shouldn't have hypen, it should be written in single word


HTML: Hypertext Markup Language
- HTML is used to structure a webpage
- HTML tags are predefined
- HTML tags are case insensitive
- HTML tags should also be closed but browser won't mind if you forgot to close any tag. 
- HTML is not a strict Language
- HTML file must have .htm or .html extension

